The paper deals with graph coloring problems, which are typically studied in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of treewidth as a parameter suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. The study of conflict-free coloring is related to graph theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG), which are also likely sub-categories.
